<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Ruth on Christian Internet Resources</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ruth/</link><description>Recent content in Ruth on Christian Internet Resources</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ruth/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Ruth 1</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ruth/chapter-01/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ruth/chapter-01/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ruth-chapter-1">Ruth Chapter 1&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="conversational-yahveh-covenant">Conversational Yahveh Covenant&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="elimelechs-family-moves-to-moab">Elimelech’s Family Moves to Moab&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Judges were ruling when a famine came over the country. A man from Bethlehem in Judah went with his wife and sons to stay in Moab. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>His name was Elimelech, his wife was Naomi, and his sons were Mahlon and Chilion, Ephrathites. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>But Elimelech died and Naomi was left with her two sons. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They married Moabite wives Orpah and Ruth. They lived there about ten years, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>and Mahlon and Chilion died too. So Naomi lost her husband and both sons.                                                                                                       &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ruth 2</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ruth/chapter-02/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ruth/chapter-02/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ruth-chapter-2">Ruth Chapter 2&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="ruth-meets-boaz">Ruth Meets Boaz&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Naomi’s husband Elimelech had a wealthy relative named Boaz. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Ruth said to Naomi, &lt;/span>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Let me go glean among the heads of grain after one that might take an interest in me.” &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Go ahead, my daughter.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>She went and gleaned behind the harvest crew. She happened to come to the part of the field that belonged to Boaz. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He came from Bethlehem and said to the crew, &lt;/span>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Yahveh be with you.” &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ruth 3</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ruth/chapter-03/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ruth/chapter-03/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ruth-chapter-3">Ruth Chapter 3&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="ruth-at-the-threshing-floor">Ruth at the Threshing Floor&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Then Naomi told her, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Let me find a permanent home for you so things will go well for you. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Isn’t Boaz our relative the one whose maids you were with? &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Take a bath, anoint yourself, put on your best clothes, and go down to the threshing floor. Don’t make yourself known to him till he’s finished eating. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Notice where he lies down and go uncover his feet and lie down. He’ll tell you what to do.” [&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>]&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ruth 4</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ruth/chapter-04/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ruth/chapter-04/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ruth-chapter-4">Ruth Chapter 4&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="ruth-39-18">Ruth 3:9-18&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="boaz-marries-ruth">Boaz Marries Ruth&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Boaz went up to the gate and sat down, and the close relative went past. He said, &lt;/span>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Come over here, &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>my&lt;/span>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> friend, and have a seat.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> He went over and sat down. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He had ten elders of the town sit down there. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He told the closest relative, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>